title: WebServer API: Get All Tiddlers
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Gets an array of all raw non-system tiddlers, excluding the ''text'' field.

```
GET /recipes/default/tiddlers.json
```

Parameters:

* ''filter'' - filter identifying tiddlers to be returned (optional, defaults to "[all[tiddlers]!is[system]sort[title]]")
* ''exclude'' - comma delimited list of fields to excluded from the returned tiddlers (optional, defaults to "text")

To avoid denial of service attacks with malformed filters by default only the following filters are permitted:

* `[all[tiddlers]] -[[$:/isEncrypted]] -[prefix[$:/temp/]] -[prefix[$:/status/]]` (the filter used by the current TiddlyWeb adaptor)
* `[all[tiddlers]!is[system]sort[title]]` (the filter used by default when the filter is not specified)

The list of permitted filters may be overridden in [[tiddlywiki.info|tiddlywiki.info Files]] in the config setting `server-get-tiddlers-allowed-filters`. For example, the following setting explicitly permits the filter used by the TiddlyWeb adaptor plugin:

```
...
"config": {
	"server-get-tiddlers-allowed-filters": [
		"[all[tiddlers]] -[[$:/isEncrypted]] -[prefix[$:/temp/]] -[prefix[$:/status/]]"
	]
}
...
```

It is also possible to configure the server to accept any filter, but this should not be done for public facing servers.

```
...
"config": {
	"server-get-tiddlers-allowed-filters": "all"
}
...
```

Response:

* 200 OK
*> `Content-Type: application/json`
*> Body: array of all non-system tiddlers in [[TiddlyWeb JSON tiddler format]] 
* 403 Forbidden
